<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<TestCaseEntity>
   <description>As an I-RMC I want to access the Details tab on the Review Submission screen so that I can view a summary of the task I want to process. 

Acceptance Criteria: 

RM-516.1: CDAT allows the user to open a task by selecting the Coversheet ID. 

RM-516.2: CDAT directs the user to the Submission Review screen which displays the following tabs: 
•Details (displayed by default) 
•Submission 

 RM-516.3: The Details tab displays the following information: 
•Coversheet ID 
•Enrollee ID 
•Name 
•Corrected Name (field does not display if name has not been changed) 
•DOB 
•Corrected DOB (field does not display if DOB has not been changed) 
•Provider Type 
•Date of Service Start 
•Date of Service End 

RM-516.4: DELETED. 

RM-516.5: CDAT displays a timeline which shows previous actions performed on the record. The latest action performed is displayed first. Note: The complete life cycle of the record is shown in Research Management. The details tab will only display comments. 

RM-516.6: CDAT allows the user to sort the timeline from newest to oldest and vice versa. 

RM-516.7: CDAT displays a date and timestamp (MM/DD/YYYY, X:XX AM/PM) for each action in the timeline. 

RM-516.8: CDAT displays the following comments when applicable: 
• All comments and escalation related comments 
• QA Panel Reset comments 
• PM Reset comment if the record was PM Reset at Submission Review 

RM-516.9: CDAT displays the user who entered each comment. 

RM-516.10: CDAT provides the option to minimize the comment(s) for each section.</description>
   <name>RM_516_Access Details Tab on Submission Review Screen</name>
